<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-559-233  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 559 233.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Office  Oct 1990 v112 n4 p108(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Optical disk technology and how to implement it. (optical disksoffer the computer advantages of sorting and processing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Waegermann, C. Peter.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Optical disks are the emerging storage technology because of theircapability to store millions of images.andP;  They provide quick anddirect access to records, the capability for several users to workon the same records simultaneously and the assurance of saferecord storage for up to 100 years.andP;  Optical disks also offersorting and processing advantages and eliminate the chance oflosing records.andP;  Optical memory storage is a legal and archivalmethod of storing records on a computer.andP;  Users are advised,however, to study the different technologies of optical diskrecording.andP;  One disk may last for 10 years, others for 100 years.andO;In purchasing a system, users must question the type of disk driveoffered, its transfer rate and the read life of the disk.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Optical DisksUser NeedsPerformance SpecificationsHardware Selection.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>